 most users had great results, some did not. Actually, the solution to the mystery is well known but not yet applied to a commercial product.Long ago, it was discovered that the body uses two chemical pathways to produce NO. Sometimes this is depicted with a Ying-and-Yang symbol, because the two paths are perceived to be a single process.The first path was utilized in the early NO products. It starts with the presence of an amino acid called L-arginine. The second pathway, however, starts with the presence of nitrates and nitrites. One of the differences is that the L-Arginine pathway becomes less functional as a person ages. This explains why some older folks did not receive maximum benefit from the original formulations. INTRODUCING CARDIO MIRACLE In 2014, the people who produce Cardio Miracle began incorporating these discoveries into a new formulation that follows both nitric-oxide pathways – and they added several high-potency anti-oxidants to enhance the second path.This is not a mix of patented chemicals claiming to contain “natural flavors” (which often means more chemicals). When you read the label, shown in the FAQ section at the end of this review, you will see that Cardio Miracle is dominantly composed of dried, non-GMO foods. The powders are derived from real fruits and vegetables and prepared with the absolute minimum of processing so as to retain nutrients. The remaining ingredients are not just vitamins, minerals, and enzymes, but also include natural substances that aid the body’s production of nitric oxide at the cellular level.In 1915, Jonathan Stamler, a professor of medicine at Case Western Reserve University School of Medicine discovered that respiration is a three-gas system involving, not just oxygen and carbon dioxide, but also nitric oxide, which controls the ability of blood vessels to expand, when needed, to increase blood flow. Without this ability to expand blood vessels on demand, such as during physical exertion or emotional stress, the delivery of oxygen will be inadequate and can lead to heart failure or stroke. See “Molecular and functional basis established for nitric oxide joining oxygen and carbon dioxide in respiratory cycle,” The Daily, Case Western Reserve University, 2015 April 30,  http://thedaily.case.edu/molecular-and-functional-basis-established-for-nitric-oxide-joining-oxygen-and-carbon-dioxide-in-respiratory-cycle You can go to the order section here For 20% discount, enter promocode neverforget on “place-order” page. THE MANY EFFECTS OF CARDIO MIRACLE Although my initial interest in this product was its ability to lower blood pressure, it soon became apparent from the testimonials we were receiving that there are many other benefits as well – and some of them are big. The following unsolicited letters from users tell the story.HIGH BLOOD PRESSURE“Since I have been using Cardio Miracle, I have not had to take blood-pressure medications. My pressure is now normal, and no side effects. Most of the time I only take 1/2 dose, and it still brings it down, usually around 127/83 or so. THIS STUFF WORKS! I am a former gym rat, and Cardio Miracle seems to tone my muscles as well. I am physically stronger with little or no working out. ” ~~ Charles Bruce“I’m fairly young but have battled high blood pressure for over 10 years. The medication I was on made it hard for me to do my job as a general contractor. I started taking Cardio Miracle and started to feel better after about a week. It’s been 10 months, my doctor took me off my blood-pressure medication, and I’m feeling better than I have in 10 years.” ~~ Russell Pincock“Hi Ed. Last week, my blood pressure was 120/68. And I am 84. Have been taking the Cardio-Miracle that you recommended for three months.The info in your books, The Creature and World Without Cancer is equal to a master’s degree in sane living.” ~~ Joe Ferguson, Utah.“As a professional chemist, I began taking several of the components of Cardio Miracle when I had a health s